==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shrievalty
<hw>Shriev"al*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Contr. from
<ets>sheriffalty</ets>. See <er>Shrieve</er>, <pos>n.</pos>
<er>Sheriff</er>.]</ety> <def>The office, or sphere of jurisdiction, of
a sheriff; sheriffalty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was ordained by 28 Edward I that the people shall have election
of sheriff in every shire where the <qex>shrievalty</qex> is not of
inheritance.</q> <rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shrieve</ent>⟦br⟧
